3.20	Voline	Volin	Vsevolod Mikhailovich Eikhenbaum (Russian: ; August 11, 1882 - September 18, 1945), known in later life as Volin or (the spelling he used himself) Voline (Во́лин), was a leading Russian anarchist who participated in the Russian and Ukrainian Revolutions before being forced into exile by the Bolshevik Party government. He was a main proponent of the anarchist organizational form known as synthesis anarchism.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/d/dc/Voline.jpg
